I don't think it fits into class balance; 5-6 wizards being able kill something that a full balanced group cannot (or cannot as reliably) is not my definition of class balance. I don't think it fits risk versus reward. Even if a lone balanced group was to take down a mob that 5-6 wizards are manaburning, they would still spend much more time porting around, buffing, and medding. All the wizards would have to do is port in, med, and get the timing of manaburn right. Sure they could fail, only if they screw up their timing though, or if they have lag/LD issues (but that can happen to anyone). Risk? Worst case scenario? Die once after maybe 20 minutes tops of porting, prepping, and pressing the click button. This is not a huge risk IMO.<br>
<br>
As with what I said before; it's the principle. I don't need Kunark dragons anymore, so I'm going to see MB wizards stealing dragon scales or haste items from me, but just because something doesn't affect you, it doesn't make it automatically ok.<br>
<br>
