MB *IS* argueably superior to those in PVP, but I'd still bet on the ranger with AM3, a pre-nerf bow of doom, trueshot and 14 damage arrows/endless quiver.  With 2k+ crits very possible AND 400ish range, rangers are the absolute bane of non horse-riding PVPers.<br>
<br>
Is it broken?  Yah, a bit, but most &quot;cool&quot; abilities are (almost by definition).  Is it unbalancing in PVP?  Yah, it'd suck to be MBed right off the bat (tho better than the damned rapture enchanters get imho).  Can it be used in unusual situations that weren't necessarily intended?  Yep, we got 10 or so MB wizzies now, I'm quite sure most kunark boss mobs were supposed to live more than 3 seconds.  <br>
<br>
But what the heck, in the end it's just a Big Nuke; back in the day, so was icecomet (which would kill most level 50's in one shot when it came out).  Not something to cry nerf about methinks.  The only real concern I have is that it'll deter/affect &quot;good&quot; small group encounters in PoPo (pronouced &quot;PooPoo&quot; btw, until proven different <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) by setting a minimum hp for decent loot mobs to 100k or so+.<br>
<br>
Just my thoughts anyway.  It's a cool ability, would hate to see the wizzies lose it, cause if I was one I'd want it too. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Hrm... maybe verant will put in a &quot;health burn&quot; effect for warriors... at 8k+ hp for the well-geared, that'd be pretty impressive. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
RdT.<br>
p.s. Ring not the bell-of-nerf, for indeed it will ring for thee as well someday. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Unless it affects rogues or gnomes of course. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uglatius2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glatius2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 185<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/19/02 10:45:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1790.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: A fight?</span><hr size=1> Nerf?  What have we got left worth nerfing?  Our broken taunt?  Our supposedly superior HP which are no longer particularly superior?  Our supposedly superior mitigation that isn't superior any longer?  Warcry?  Area taunt?  There isn't anything in the Warrior arsenal worth nerfing.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=remfdatroll>Remf da Troll</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 222<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/19/02 10:58:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1790.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: A fight?</span><hr size=1> Painful personal experience... there's Always Something Else they can nerf.<br>
